Behavioral Model of EYE Monitor and TX Calibration

config_nominal contains run variables 
config_sweep contains swept TX settings to sample eye from

commands:
python eye_mon.engine config_nominal.json
python eye_mon.sweep config_sweep.json

Goal is to model TX FIR, channel FIR, and Frontend BW/nonlinearity with PI for eye reconstruction.
A sweep will report the winner TX FIR settings that optimize eye height and eye area for an oracle run (no sampling jitter)
and compare to sampling jitter included eye reconstructions. If jittery eye reconstructions converge to oracle winner, we can determine
at which level of sampling jitter is acceptable. 


